Felix Mendelssohn (1809-1847) wrote his Fantasie, Op. 28, also titled Sonata Ã©cossaise (Scottish sonata) in 1833, with dedication to Ignaz Moscheles (1794-1870). It is a work in three movements, in the key of F sharp minor, and it was published in 1834.

[0:00] I. Con moto agitato
[5:41] II. Allegro con moto 
[7:47] III. Presto
